{"name": "st-tailwind", "metadata": {"name": "st_tailwind", "version": "1.0.6", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["streamlit"], "summary": "Python tailwind toolkit - Injected with JS", "upload_time": 1734952526}, "documentation": ["# Streamlit Tailwind\r\n\r\n## If you find this project useful, please consider leaving a star <3\r\n\r\nThis project, Streamlit Tailwind, is designed to simplify the process of creating user interfaces. It provides a straightforward way to incorporate Tailwind CSS into your Streamlit\r\napplications. So, without further ado:\r\n\r\n## Install\r\n\r\nSame as always, good ol' pip (or equivalents)\r\n\r\n```sh\r\npip install st_tailwind\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Example\r\n\r\n![img.png](static/img.png)\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport streamlit as st\r\n\r\nimport st_tailwind as tw\r\n\r\nst.set_page_config(\"Streamlit Tailwind Examples\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    tw.initialize_tailwind()\r\n\r\n    tw.write(\"Grid Container\", classes=\"text-blue-500 pb-4\")\r\n    with tw.container(classes=\"grid grid-cols-4\"):\r\n        for idx in range(1, 9):\r\n            st.button(f\"Button {idx}\")\r\n\r\n    tw.write(\"Colored Button\", classes=\"text-purple-500 pb-4\")\r\n    tw.button(\"Button\", classes=\"bg-red-500\")\r\n\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    main()\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\n### Initialization\r\n\r\nAfter configuring your page, call the initialize function so tailwind can be injected as a dependency.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport streamlit as st\r\n\r\nimport st_tailwind as tw\r\n\r\nst.set_page_config(\"Streamlit Tailwind Examples\")\r\n\r\ntw.initialize_tailwind()\r\n```\r\n\r\n### First way:\r\n\r\nUse the tailwind wrapper components.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport st_tailwind as tw\r\n\r\ntw.selectbox(\"test\", [], classes=\"w-fit\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Second way:\r\n\r\nWrap the component yourself. You can add the `classes` keyword argument either in the wrapper method or on the wrapped method.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport streamlit as st\r\n\r\nfrom st_tailwind import tw_wrap\r\n\r\ntw_wrap(st.selectbox, classes=\"w-fit\")(\"test\", [])\r\ntw_wrap(st.selectbox)(\"test\", [], classes=\"w-fit\")\r\n```\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "st_tailwind.const", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "st_tailwind.const.correspondence", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "st_tailwind.resources", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "st_tailwind.resources.frontend", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "st_tailwind", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "st_tailwind.button", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.button", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.checkbox", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.checkbox", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.columns", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.columns", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.container", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.container", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.data_editor", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.data_editor", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.dataframe", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.dataframe", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.date_input", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.date_input", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.divider", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.divider", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.download_button", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.download_button", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.file_uploader", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.file_uploader", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.multiselect", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.multiselect", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_tailwind.progress", "xref": {"fqname": "st_tailwind.progress", "project": null}}, {"name": "st_